==English==

===Etymology===
From the name of the Thaypan tribe of Aboriginal people of central [[Cape York Peninsula]], [[Queensland]], [[Australia]].

===Noun===
'''taipan''' (''plural:'' '''[[taipans]]''')

Extremely venemous species of snakes of the family ''[[Elapidae]]''; the Coastal Taipan (''Oxyuranus scutellatus scutellatus''), and the Inland Taipan or Fierce Snake, (''Oxyuranus microlepidotus''). Both species are found in Australia, while a subspecies of the Coastal Taipan, (''Oxyuranus scutellatus canniis''), is found in southern coastal [[New Guinea]].


